node.text:
@thelistshowtv  interviewed me and asked me for some tips to give parents whose children’s are returning back to school after remote learning.

Things are constantly changing and I don’t have all of the answers but hopefully some of these tips are helpful to you :)

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by MoNique Waters ♡🦋 in Cleveland, Ohio with @masonscreamery. May be an image of 1 person, icecream, gelato and outdoors.

node.text:
🍦🍨
They say “you are what you eat”
If that’s the case…
I am pumpkin & ube ice cream
with peanut butter whip cream
in an egg waffle from @masonscreamery
during SummerWeen 🤎

#icecreamismylovelanguage #icecream #summer #summervacation #cle #cleveland #teachersofthegram

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by MoNique Waters ♡🦋 on July 28, 2021 tagging @simonebiles, and @ashton.creates. May be an illustration of one or more people and text.

node.text:
🙌🏽✨
“Take care of number one”

My grandma always use to say this to me every time we got off the phone. I truly understand the value of her words and find myself repeating them in my head often.

node.text:
🌈🦄
“I used to dislike being sensitive.
I thought it made me weak.
But take away that single trait, and you take away the very essence of who I am.
You take away my conscience, my ability to empathize, my intuition, my creativity, my deep appreciation of the little things, my vivid inner life, my keen awareness of others pain and my passion for it all.”

I saw this quote and felt every word. This little girl use to cry and feel all the feels.. i still do.

I remember being called a cry baby or being told “it’s not a big deal” and hating that I felt things so deeply.

I’m so glad that I never lost that part of me.

What is the one thing that you use to dislike about yourself that you have grown to love?

node.text:
💕✌🏽
Our students won’t remember that textbook math lesson & just the same I the teacher won’t remember the same old boring Professional Development.

I will remember the ones where I felt seen and heard, where I collaborated, listened, and learned.

I’ll remember the ones where I laughed and maybe even cried.

The ones where I finally found someone whose done it and gets it.

The PD that taught me to think outside of the box and reminded me of my WHY.

I’ll remember the PD where friendships and memories were made. The nights spent talking with people who were once a stranger that now feel like family.

These are the PDs that I will remember and for that I am thankful!

node.text:
✨✨
You wanna know what I love about this week, about this conference and all of the amazing educators here?!?

I love that we are able to collaborate, learn, grow, step out of our comfort zone all while having the time of our lives.

I leave here with new strategies, content, lessons, materials and resources that are all research based and effective all while making new friends and having sooo much fun!

I love that I feel valuable and appreciated!
I love that I am engaged and interested in what I am actually learning.
I love the energy!
I love all the love.

@getyourteachon is more than just a PD it is how I fill my cup, how I refuel, and how I grow as an educator and a person.

Having the opportunity to present this year made the experience next level amazing. I love teaching and learning and I’m just so thankful and blessed to be here.
.
.
#teachersofinstagram #teachersfollowteachers #getyourteachon #gytoxorlando
